""
"there is little doubt in my mind that this is one of, if not the single best straight up quad i have ever had made in america. the other beers in this series were starting to get out there a bit, pineapple juice, gooseberriers, and so on, so its nice to get grounded a little here. dark rum colored brew, with red and brown in the light, and a tall frothy head indicative of the style. it smells like tons of dried fruit, raisins and cherries and dates, i get the candy sugar too, molasses, and booze, and the belgian yeast is fruity but not over the top in its ester intensity. the flavor is just like the nose, with all the fruits coming through, its a touch tannic like a diluted red wine, but its flattering to the overall. the booze does show up in the finish, especially as it warms, but i still wouldnt have placed it over 10% abv. there is a nice richness and creaminess of feel that makes it a great holiday beer, but im not sure i would age this one, i cant imagine any part of the experience improving over time. world class quad, interesting and hearty, memorable for me."
