"Aroma of brown sugar, molasses and a bit of sweet chocolate/cherry.  Bit of cocoa powder after a bit of agitation tends to see the light through the sweet notes.   Taste is slick and oily initially and when cold but gathers some traction with warming and exposure, yeilding more Belgian yeast character and some more subtle complexities.  Feel is expected given the nose and taste, that being a bit sweet and viscous with moderate complexity.  Overall a bit one sided and somewhat limited in nature though will likely improve with a couple years of quiet time.  Personally prefer Quads a bit drier but this doesn't disappoint either."
